commentTextItems.html: played uppishly, well over Kumble at midwicket, Kumble runs for it, but can't reach the ball, West Indies have won the match

commentPostTextItems.html: third place cheque to Zimbabwe USD 10,000 since Zimbabwe have already left, the cheque is collected by SCA runners-up cheque, USD 25,000 to Tendulkar

Tendulkar: "we were in a very good position... Rahul batted well, Choipra batted well, also Ganguly batted well but for West Indies Ricardo Powell batted so well, it was one of the best innings I had seen talks about Mohanty's bowling performance unfortunately we couldn't bring the cup home, but hopefully the next time...

one of the spectators who caught a six is presented with S$ 250 Ricardo Powell gets USD 500 for the fastest fifty man of the match award. to Ricardo Powell. USD 2000 USD 4000 for Ricardo Powell, for man of the series Powell: says his hitting is not as much about strength but about hitting it correctly his team mates congratulating Powell Ridley Jacobs getting a prize - ICICI safe hands of the match award USD 30,000 to Lara and West Indies for winning the challenge here Coca-Cola Singapore Challenge Trophy presented to Lara Lara hopes to keep this form and take it to Toronto a special mention for Walsh that is it people. We will bring you the Toronto cricket festival as well as the Australia in Sri Lanka Test matches, live good bye

commentTextItems.html: on the stumps, pushed to short midwicket
played through the covers, that takes West Indies close to the victory
played to midon, straight to the fielder
turned straight to midwicket Robin Singh
comes forward, played to midwicket, well fielded by Robin Singh at midwicket
turned to fineleg, quick running Jimmy Adams is the runner for Perry
on the stumps, played back to the bowler
on the stumps, forward, rapped on the pads

played to long off, keeps the strike
